{"word":"κλοιός","slug":"κλοιός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κλοιός</b></el> <el>(κλοιός, οῦ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>κλείω</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a dog-collar</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>a large wooden collar</i>, put on mischievous dogs, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a</i> sort of <i>pillory</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><el>χρύσεος κλ.</el> <i>a collar</i> of gold, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}